        "Education Standards" : "<p>In 2006, a statewide task force consisting of representatives from both the public and private sector developed Wisconsin's Model Academic Standards for Personal and Financial Literacy. These standards are rigorous and are to be used by local districts and teachers as guidelines (but are not mandatory) for developing local grade-by-grade curriculum. See: <a href=\"https://dpi.wi.gov/finance/standards\" target=\"_blank\">Wisconsin Personal Finance Standards</a>.<br /><em></em></p>",
